Date: Tue, 1 Apr 1997 14:19:32 +1000 (GMT+1000)
From: papproci@dingo.cc.uq.oz.au
Robert A. LaBudde asked: "How do you immunize against E. coli O157:H7 or S.
typhimurium? When only 25-100 organisms can overload an immature or weakened
immune system?", and Karl Bettelheim said: "It is not just E. coli O157, it
is all the other toxigenic E.coli carried that matter." Perhaps even more
pertinent questions, to those who contemplate developing a vaccine, is:
"Whom do we vaccinate?", and: "Who will pay for the vaccination?"
