[3]
From: JSCHENTA@mfhs.edu (Schentag, Jerome)
Date: Tue, 01 Apr 1997 12:02:43 -0500
Which antibiotics is the organism resistant to?? It makes a difference!
Some antibiotics stop the release of endotoxin, while others promote it, so
it makes a big difference which active agent is used. On the basis of
treating humans with ecoli infections, I do not necessarily agree that all
antibiotics should worsen this problem. Usually, it is better to kill the
bacteria, especially with an antibiotic that does not release more
endotoxin...
---
Jerome Schentag
